abstract: The pledge by the former New York City mayor is part of an effort to close every coal-fired power plant in the United States and halt the growth of natural gas.
snippet: The pledge by the former New York City mayor is part of an effort to close every coal-fired power plant in the United States and halt the growth of natural gas.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON â€” Michael R. Bloomberg, the former mayor of New York City, said on Friday he would donate $500 million to a new campaign to close every coal-fired power plant in the United States and halt the growth of natural gas.

abstract: President Trump said not enough progress was made in meetings between the Mexican and U.S. governments but that talks would resume on Thursday.
snippet: President Trump said not enough progress was made in meetings between the Mexican and U.S. governments but that talks would resume on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: Updated June 6, 2019: After this story was published, officials from Customs and Border Protection said on Thursday that illegal border crossings have risen to a 13-year high, not a seven-year high as they had reported earlier.

headline_main: N.Y.C. Is Getting Safer, but Hate Crimes Are Up

abstract: The 30th anniversary of the pro-democracy protests has prompted a censorship wave in China. Refinitiv, a data company partly owned by Reuters, complied.
snippet: The 30th anniversary of the pro-democracy protests has prompted a censorship wave in China. Refinitiv, a data company partly owned by Reuters, complied.
lead_paragraph: A financial-information company partly owned by the news organization Thomson Reuters removed articles related to the June 4, 1989, Tiananmen Square massacre from the feeds of its data terminals in China last week. The move came under pressure from the Chinese government, Reuters reported Monday.

abstract: The CFDA Awards featured inclusivity, Jennifer Lopez and a literal passing of the torch.
snippet: The CFDA Awards featured inclusivity, Jennifer Lopez and a literal passing of the torch.
lead_paragraph: So much for politics. After two years in which the CFDA awards â€” the annual celebrity-and-model-infused â€œOscars of the Fashion Worldâ€ bestowed by the Council of Fashion Designers of America â€” had celebrated and called out the need for diversity, the power of immigrants, the rights of women and questioned the very meaning of what it was to be a designer; on an evening that symbolized the turn of an era as Diane von Furstenberg, the longtime CFDA chairman, passed the torch of leadership (literally) to Tom Ford; at a ceremony where more designers of color were nominated for awards than possibly ever before, the winner was â€¦ the status quo.

abstract: After years of failed efforts to enact federal universal background checks for new gun purchases, several candidates are on the leading edge of a push for more aggressive anti-gun measures
snippet: After years of failed efforts to enact federal universal background checks for new gun purchases, several candidates are on the leading edge of a push for more aggressive anti-gun measures
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON â€” For the first time in two decades, Democratic presidential candidates are engaged in a politically fraught debate on gun-control policy as campaigns and advocacy groups assess the nationâ€™s evolving views of an issue long considered a land mine for the left.
